media$title.$t: ASL Master Song Performer - Chris Bahl

media$description.$t:
At the Ocean City, NJ Show, ASL Comedian Keith Wann invited fellow coda and ASL Performer Chris Bahl to take the stage and share a song in ASL.  Chris was able to showcase his skills and talents and the Deaf Audience gave him a standing hand wave ovation when he was done.
Chris Bahl travels the ASL Nation, both performing and teaching others how to incorporate ASL into their songs.  To book Chris for your event - Mecodaterp@gmail.com

Chris Bahl's Current Bio:
Bahl is involved with the Gallaudet University football program. He started as the American Sign Language interpreter for Coach Chuck Goldstein when he was the offensive coordinator in 2009. Bahl currently is the man behind the scenes working with all aspects of the program as he runs the football operations side for the Bison.

The Faribault, Minn., native has also served as a team interpreter for the Gallaudet women's basketball program from 2009-11. In his spare time he works as an ASL interpreter, performer, and teacher. He has strong ties to the Deaf Community as both of his parents are deaf and his sister is also an ASL interpreter. Bahl currently resides in Ocean City, NJ.

Mecodaterp@gmail.com

title.$t: Keith Wann's Challenge "Angry Dad in ASL"

media$title.$t: Keith Wann's Challenge "Angry Dad in ASL"

media$description.$t:
Sign Language Access Inc - THE ANGRY DAD
"Giving back to the ASL Community"
This particular clip that we have added ASL to has been in the newspaper and media this past week, and the video itself reached 27 million views.  Parents support it, Psychologists are against it.
ASL Music videos are nice...for happy happy, but where is the real stuff?  The news, information, stories, poems, events, and other things that can benefit the ASL Community as a whole for us all to share, network, and inform - we need more ASL videos on YouTube.
Challenge to ASL Students - upload for us all to share, not music, but something that gives back to the community, the community that has taught you the beautiful, rich, expressive, and real language of ASL.

Sign Language Access Inc

We do NOT have the audio because we want you to support the original Video and view it at this link - 

http://www.facebook.com/tommyjordaniii/posts/299559803434210

title.$t: The Storyteller with Keith Wann - it's just a sign for a word!

media$title.$t: The Storyteller with Keith Wann - it's just a sign for a word!

media$description.$t:
A narrative or story in its broadest sense is anything told or recounted; more narrowly, and more usually, something told or recounted in the form of a causally-linked set of events; account; tale,: the telling of a happening or connected series of happenings, whether true or fictitious. 

Storytelling is the conveying of events in words, images and sounds, often by improvisation or embellishment. Stories or narratives have been shared in every culture as a means of entertainment, education, cultural preservation and in order to instill moral values. Crucial elements of stories and storytelling include plot, characters and narrative point of view.

Use the language as it should be used...go for the concept and meaning when interpreting

ASL Storyteller/Comedian/Actor
Keith Wann
www.KeithWann.com

title.$t: ICEWORM: the Original ASL Improv group with Keith Wann, Crom Saunders, and Wormy

media$title.$t: ICEWORM: the Original ASL Improv group with Keith Wann, Crom Saunders, and Wormy

media$description.$t:
This was created in 2007 when ICEWORM took over the Deaf Cruise with 4000 ASL fans.  We were the entertainment group, had our own television show, hosted events - and mostly did improv the whole time for little pay.
Enjoy the short clips and half naked men....

in 2002 Crom Saunders and Justin "Wormy" Callaway started ICEWORM, by hosting ASL improv parties and events and in 2003 Keith Wann joined and the trio took off touring across the Nation.  Many hours of hilarious improv and skits were performed on the stage and behind closed doors.  ICEWORM launched the solo careers of Keith Wann and Crom Saunders.  Coming in 2012 the ICEWORM:the Beginnings DVD will be coming out allowing you to see the original and hilarious ASL improv that traveled up and down the West and East Coast of the ASL Nation

media$description.$t:
You might notice my awesome shirt - "Language For All" is a grassroots marketing campaign to help raise awareness and funds for the benefit of Texas School for the Deaf.  just like many Deaf Schools, they've face pretty harsh budget cuts and they need YOUR support!  The first thing you should do is 'like' their facebook page at www.facebook.com/LanguageForAll

"We, the people of Texas, are on the verge of failing a critical part of our community. State budget cuts are threatening access to language for deaf children, and it is our shared responsibility to make sure they retain this fundamental right. Unite with the Texas School for the Deaf as we transform lives through our language and education services. Join us in our relentless crusade to fight for Language for All."

SUPPORTED by ASL Comedian Performer Keith Wann
www.KeithWann.com

media$title.$t: Blossom Montessori School for the Deaf

media$description.$t:
ASL celebration day at the St. Pete Pier, Nov 12, 2011
www.BlossomSchool.org
We invite you to visit our innovative and exciting academic environment for children who are deaf or hard of hearing. In addition, unlike other traditional deaf programs, Blossom also enrolls children who are hearing and have deaf siblings, and children with deaf parents. We have also opened our doors 'a little wider' to a limited number of hearing children without a connection to the Deaf community. With this new outreach, students learn and grow in an environment that offers them a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to understand a culture much different from their own, and to learn American Sign Language, a language that transcends all geographic barriers. Blossom is different and Blossom makes a difference in the lives of children.

title.$t: Llama Llama Red Pajama ASL with Keith Wann

media$title.$t: Llama Llama Red Pajama ASL with Keith Wann

media$description.$t:
Millions of children in low-income neighborhoods are at risk of school failure before they even start kindergarten. Jumpstart's Read for the Record®, presented in partnership with the Pearson Foundation, allows Americans to demand that all children receive the quality early education they deserve.
On October 6, 2011, more than 2 million voices will call for an end to America's early education achievement gap by reading Llama Llama Red Pajama by Anna Dewdney -- setting a world record in the process! Pledge to read at www.readfortherecord.org.
Sit Down to Read
On October 6, Jumpstart's Read for the Record kicks off on NBC's TODAY show. On that day, thousands of reading events will be hosted by governors, mayors, schools, businesses, libraries, individuals and other organizations—all to raise awareness of the early education achievement gap. All the tools needed to plan a reading event -- big or small -- can be found at www.readfortherecord.org.
Want to read Llama Llama Red Pajama online? Through We Give Books and Pearson Foundation, you can read Llama Llama Red Pajama for free on at www.wegivebooks.org/readfortherecord. Every online reader will help Pearson Foundation donate books to children in need!
Stand Up for Children
By joining the campaign, you'll help us call for an end to America's early education achievement gap! In low-income neighborhoods, children start kindergarten behind their wealthier peers -- and research shows that most will never catch up. This achievement gap means that millions of children are not fulfilling their potential.
High quality early education is the best way to set our children -- and our nation -- on a path for long-term success. By joining the campaign, you'll be supporting Jumpstart, a national early education organization that helps preschool children in low-income neighborhoods develop the language and literacy skills they need for school, setting them on a path to close the achievement gap. Learn more at www.jstart.org.

title.$t: Keith Wann's ASL Radio show - Deaf Friendly!  True biz???

media$title.$t: Keith Wann's ASL Radio show - Deaf Friendly!  True biz???

media$description.$t:
Wann and Wink host a weekly ASL Radio show done live from the Wann Studios in Clearwater FL, and broadcast to the listening nation every Weds Night from 8 to 9 pm EST - Live-Captioning is provided during the show and then the next day Wann and Wink work on uploading the ASL Video Version so the Deaf fans who missed the show can still catch it later - along with the Audio version for the Signing-Impaired held at Itunes Podcasts
Tune in today www.KeithWann.com, and then click on radio tab
or go directly to the radio website page www.Toginet.com/show/thatkeithwannshowculturalbridges

A sample of past guests include:
Jack Jason
Peter Cook
Terrylene and Deanne Bray
Sherry Hicks
Ken Davis
Crom Saunders
Cheryl Moose
Dr. ALan Marcus
Antonio Goodwin
Lianna Carrera
Jeremy Jack
Matt Marquis
and many more..

This show is also a great learning place for ASL for students learning our language - they can watch the ASL version (without voice) and improve their receptive skills while also learning about topics that are important to us in the ASL Community!

Come build Cultural Bridges with us every Weds nite!

title.$t: Snafu in the Park DVD with Keith Wann preview

media$title.$t: Snafu in the Park DVD with Keith Wann preview

media$description.$t:
Order your Snafu in the Park DVD now!!!
http://www.keithwann.com/KW/Products.html

The "ASL 4 Life" series promotes a fun way to learn languages. 
In Snafu in the Park, Snafu attempts to have picnic with his new friend. Come learn from the lovable character, with a good heart, who bumbles around life while innocent chaos unfolds.  
Watch this DVD and share a fun time with family and friends as you learn over 100 words in American Sign Language, English, and Spanish.
 
There are 3 tracks to choose from - the Story, the Story with inserted Vocabulary, and Vocabulary.
Voice-over in Spanish and English for Vocabulary.
